5|$|As {{the press}} conference had been {{broadcast}} live, within hours, thousands of people gathered at <b>the</b> <b>Berlin</b> <b>Wall</b> demanding that the guards open the gates. The border guards were unable to contact their superiors for instructions and, fearing a stampede, opened the gates. The iconic scenes that followed– people pouring into West Berlin, standing on the Wall and attacking it with pickaxes– were broadcast worldwide.|$|E
